MacOS Prerequisites to run pp.py

1) Homebrew (if not installed)
   /bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"

2) Install system packages
   brew install python
   brew install --cask firefox
   brew install geckodriver

3) Create & activate a virtual environment (recommended)
   python3 -m venv .venv
   source .venv/bin/activate

4) Install Python dependencies
   If there is a `requirements.txt` in the repo root:
       pip install -r requirements.txt
   Otherwise install the essentials:
       pip install pandas selenium openpyxl

5) Verify installations
   geckodriver --version
   firefox --version
   python -c "import pandas, selenium; print('ok')"

6) Prepare config and data
   - Ensure `config.json` exists (the script will create a default one).
   - Edit `config.json` and set `"automation_allowed": true` to enable automation.
   - Place `PiratePunisher_WebsiteList.xlsx` in the repository root; it should contain a column with site URLs (header like `URLs`).

7) Run
   python pp.py

Notes
- `tkinter` is included with most macOS Python builds; if missing, install a Python distribution that includes it.
- If you prefer Chrome, the script is written for Firefox/geckodriver â€” adapting to Chrome requires changing the WebDriver setup.
